	the defective thermostats I've seen have failed in the open
position, which would keep the flaps pushed open.

	I clean them, then test them before installing them (drop in pan
of hot water, see if they expand, then contract when pulled out of the
hot water)   All the bad ones I found seemed to be permantly expanaded,
I didn't find any that would stay closed.




